Wuyang Zhang

Bio

Wuyang Zhang, MHS is a first-year PhD student at the Epidemiology Department of Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health. His research interests include age-related hearing loss and other sensory loss, family caregiving, and social determinants of health.

Education

Johns Hopkins University | Baltimore, MD

PhD in Epidemiology | September 2024 - Present

Johns Hopkins University | Baltimore, MD

MHS in Epidemiology | September 2020 - May 2022

Renmin University of China | Beijing, China

B.S. in Social Welfare | September 2016 - May 2020

Experience

Johns Hopkins Cochlear Center for Hearing and Public Health | Research Data Analyst | July 2022 - July 2024
